Need to enable non-interactive SSH.

Here is the only working approach accroding to Paul Huang:

Use ssh-keygen to generate a private and public key pair.

ssh-keygen -t dsa
(or ssh-keygen -t rsa)

The files will be placed in id_dsa and id_dsa.pub under ~/.ssh

Then just append the file id_dsa.pub to the end of ~/.ssh/authorized_keys:
cat id_dsa.pub >> authorized_keys


